cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper is about improving the energy efficiency and lifespan of wireless sensor networks through clustering and optimized selection of cluster heads. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the problem of energy depletion and throughput, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of regions and optimized selection of cluster heads could also be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
